Project structure:

├── src/
│   ├── main/
│   │   └── java/
│   │       └── com/
│   │           └── example/
│   │               └── twoSum/
│   │                   ├── Solution.java          # Main logic to solve the Two-Sum problem
│   │                   └── NoValidPairFoundException.java  # Custom exception
│   └── test/
│       └── java/
│           └── com/
│               └── example/
│                   └── twoSum/
│                       └── SolutionTest.java     # JUnit test cases for the Two-Sum problem
├── target/                # Maven target folder (generated after build)
├── .gitignore             # Git ignore file
├── LICENSE                # License file (optional, can be MIT, Apache, etc.)
├── pom.xml                # Maven build file (contains dependencies, plugins, etc.)
└── README.md              # Project documentation

Explanation:
src/main/java/com/example/twoSum/Solution.java: Contains the main logic for solving the Two-Sum problem.
src/main/java/com/example/twoSum/NoValidPairFoundException.java: A custom exception for handling cases where no valid sum pair is found.
src/test/java/com/example/twoSum/SolutionTest.java: Contains the JUnit test cases that verify the solution works correctly for various scenarios.
target/: Maven build output folder that contains compiled classes and other build artifacts (this is generated automatically by Maven).
.gitignore: This file is used to ignore specific files and folders (such as target/ and .m2/) from being committed to Git.
LICENSE: The project’s license file (optional, but useful for open-source projects).
pom.xml: The Maven project object model file that defines the project, its dependencies, build configuration, etc.
README.md: Provides information about the project, how to use it, and its structure.